# Analysis Code

This repository contains code for simulating Mollow spectra using classical stochastic differential equations.
In addition, it includes code that couples classical stochastic differential equations for an optically driven two-level system to a one-dimensional FDTD solver with first-order Mur boundary conditions.

## Requirements
- Matlab (Version 2024b was used)

## Usage
demomollow01.m   change parameters at the top of the code, output: Mollow spectra obtained from quantum regression theorem, green's propagator and stochastic approach for varying detuning or Rabi energy.
demofdtd01.m     change parameters at the top of the code, output: detuned Mollow spectrum obtained from FDTD propagated classical stochastic electric fields in comprison to unpropagated Mollow spectra from stochastic approach.
